Official Documentation : https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/docker/
Version : 2.5

Jenkins is an open-source automation server used mainly for CI/CD (Continuous Integration & Continuous Delivery).
It automates building, testing, and deploying applications, making software delivery faster and more reliable.

ðŸ”¹ Jenkins Usage
1. CI/CD Pipelines

Automates your software build â†’ test â†’ deploy workflow.

Supports both:
Freestyle jobs (simple tasks).
Pipeline as Code (Jenkinsfile, scripted or declarative).

2. Integration with Source Control

Connects with GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, SVN.
Automatically triggers builds on pull requests, merges, or branch updates.

3. Automated Testing

Run unit tests, integration tests, UI tests automatically.
Generate reports (JUnit, Allure, etc.).

4. Build Automation

Compile code (Java, Node.js, Python, Go, .NET).
Build Docker images and push to registries.

5. Deployment Automation

Deploy apps to:
Kubernetes (kubectl/Helm)
Docker Compose / Swarm
AWS, GCP, Azure, DigitalOcean
Bare-metal or VM servers
